name: Ornamental Opossum
description:
A young Opossum settles into the branches of a Lilac to prepare for a post-snack snooze after feeding on a cache of crab apples stored under the snow. (Didelphis virginiana)

2016. Nikon D60, 55-200mm Lens.

Photographed in situ, without the use of artificial lighting or staging. Photoshop only used for resizing.

1024x685 300dpi jpeg
